    "name": "WordPress Publisher",
    "tagline": "Publishes news.article items from the Item Bus to your WordPress site via the REST API.",
    "description": "A consumer worker that subscribes to `news.article` items on the BFrost Item Bus and turns each one into a WordPress post. Supports configurable publish status (draft, publish, pending), custom post types, and per-run deduplication so the same article is never posted twice.\n\nThis is a real, working reference worker shipped with the BFrost repository. Copy it from `workers/examples/wordpress-publisher/` into your `workers/local/` directory to get started.",
